ify.com/s/files/1/0790/5974/7140/files/Frame_10362_a002409b-60f3-4619-84f4-f5a38cb863c8.jpg?v=1770633968&width=2048 2048w" fetchPriority="low" decoding="async" loading="lazy" style="--pf-image-ratio:1.3183098591549296" sizes="75vw" data-pf-type="Image5" class="sc-jwZJYP clbmpw pf-61_ pf-image-1" store="[object Object]"/></div><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-kpKSlO brELaQ pf-62_"><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-kpKSlO brELaQ pf-63_ pf-hide"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLsJvT gbBbPZ pf-64_ pf-heading-1-h3">Why Most Skincare and Concealers Don’t Work for these problems..</h3></div><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-kpKSlO brELaQ pf-66_"><p class="sc-stwUW giqUXE pf-67_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-fd08de68-ee0f-43b1-8589-e9a73526c9f2"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>1.&nbsp;Skincare rarely delivers what they promise</strong><strong><br></strong></span></p><p class="sc-stwUW giqUXE pf-70_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-09e6018b-de53-4818-81fc-b9f16c9a6cbc"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Men try countless creams, serums, and treatments, yet <strong>nothing&nbsp;fixes the visible issues.</strong><strong><br></strong></span></p></div><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-kpKSlO brELaQ pf-73_"><p class="sc-stwUW giqUXE pf-74_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-0bead085-c5f9-47f9-8180-b6171aa0839d"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>2. Most routines are too complicated to stick with</strong><strong><br></strong></span></p><p class="sc-stwUW giqUXE pf-77_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-a61cebab-4d8b-4089-8489-a33156b2fe99"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Most routines involve <strong>5–10 steps, multiple products</strong>, and weeks of consistency.&nbsp;</span></p></div><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-kpKSlO brELaQ pf-80_"><p class="sc-stwUW giqUXE pf-81_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-3613198a-a153-41e3-bccb-9659dd51f4d9"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>3. Women’s make-up looks obvious and shiny</strong><strong><br></strong></span></p><p class="sc-stwUW giqUXE pf-84_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-49be41bd-e5b9-41be-9066-fb8ede8126ee"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Most formulas are built for thinner, smoother skin, so on men they can <strong>look heavy, reflective, and easy to notice in real life</strong>.<strong><br></strong></span></p></div><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-kpKSlO brELaQ pf-87_"><p class="sc-stwUW giqUXE pf-88_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-bc44a6e6-2385-4ef9-bba0-67326c1ce1d1"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>4. Most products were never designed for men<br></strong></span></p><p class="sc-stwUW giqUXE pf-91_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-ba0081f5-8f67-4299-81ed-dda547ee09fa"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Men’s skin is thicker and oilier, yet most products aren’t made for it&nbsp;which is why they often <strong>sit on top, clog pores, or feel wrong with daily use</strong>.<strong><br></strong></span></p></div></div></div></section><section data-section-id="pf-0506" data-pf-type="FlexSection" class="sc-cKXyOM gdMpOS pf-94_ pf-color-scheme-1 pf-container-1"><div class="sc-bHnkpz ffFBJG pf-flex-section"><div data-pf-type="FlexBlock" class="sc-kpKSlO brELaQ pf-95_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLsJvT gbBbPZ pf-96_ pf-heading-1-h3 italic_style">KLYR VS MAKE-UP<br>WHAT'S&nbsp;THE DIFFERENCE?<br></h3><div data-pf-type="Table2" class="sc-kBRnVi eNKpXl pf-98_"><table class="pf-table-inner"><colgroup data-pf-type="Table2.ColumnBody" class="sc-kuVMvl bBmUMO pf-113_"><col span="1" data-pf-type="Table2.Column" class="sc-laNFUy ymAQo pf-114_"/><col span="1" data-pf-type="Table2.Colu